.nh
.TH "NBFC-SERVICE.JSON" 5 "APRIL 2026" "Notebook FanControl @VERSION@"
.SH NAME
.PP
nbfc_service.json \- Notebook FanControl service configuration

.SH CONFIGURATION

.BR NOTE :
Comments can be added in any JSON object by using the
.B Comment
or the
.B #
field.
.RE

.SS ServiceConfig
.PP
Main configuration file of nbfc_service
.RI ( @SYSCONFDIR@/nbfc/nbfc.json ).

.PP
.BR SelectedConfigId :
.I String
.RS
The selected config model. This equals the basename of a notebook model configuration file. Absolute file paths can also be specified.
.RE

.PP
.BR EmbeddedControllerType :
.I String
.RS
Selects the implementation used to access the embedded controller.
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
.BR ec_sys :
Use the ec_sys kernel module.
.IP \(bu 2
.BR acpi_ec :
Use the acpi_ec kernel module.
.IP \(bu 2
.BR dev_port :
Access the embedded controller via /dev/port.
.IP \(bu 2
.BR dummy :
Do not access the embedded controller at all.

.RE
If not given, the embedded controller type will be automatically selected.
.RE

.PP
.BR FanTemperatureSources :
.I Array of FanTemperatureSourceConfig
.RS
Used for configuring which sensors are attached to a fan.
.RE

.SS FanTemperatureSourceConfig
.PP
Configures which sensors are attached to a fan.
.PP
.BR FanIndex :
.IR Integer " >= 0 && " Integer " <= 255"
.RS
Specify which fan should be configured.
.RE

.PP
.BR TemperatureAlgorithmType :
.I String
.RS
See
.BR FanConfiguration \-> TemperatureAlgorithmType .
.RE

.PP
.BR Sensors :
.I Array of String
.RS
See
.BR FanConfiguration \-> Sensors .
.RE

.SS ServiceState
.PP
State file of the service
.RI ( @RUNSTATEDIR@/nbfc/state.json ).
.PP
.BR TargetFanSpeeds :
.I Array of Float
.RS
This holds the fixed speed of the fans. A value of
.B \-1
means the fan should be left in auto mode.
.RE

.SS ModelConfig
.PP
.BR NotebookModel :
.I String
.RS
The Notebook Model as described in your BIOS. See
.B nbfc get\-model\-name.
.RE

.PP
.BR Author :
.I String
.RS
The Author of the config file. Enter whatever you want.
.RE

.PP
.BR LegacyTemperatureThresholdsBehaviour :
.I Boolean
.RS
This option was introduced for beeing backwards compatible with configuration files from the original NBFC project.
The default is
.BR false .
Do not use this option for new configuration files.
.RE

.PP
.BR EcPollInterval :
.IR Integer " > 0"
.RS
Defines how often NBFC polls the EC for changes (in milliseconds).
.RE

.PP
.BR CriticalTemperature :
.I Integer
.RS
If the temperature exceeds this threshold, NBFC will ignore all Temperature threshold elements and set the fan to 100% speed until the temperature drops below
.RB ( CriticalTemperature " minus " CriticalTemperatureOffset ).
.RE

.PP
.BR CriticalTemperatureOffset :
.IR Integer " > 0"
.RS
See
.BR CriticalTemperature .
.RE

.PP
.BR ReadWriteWords :
.I Boolean
.RS
If
.BR true ,
NBFC will combine two 8 bit registers to one 16\-bit register when reading from or writing to the EC registers.
.RE

.PP
.BR LuaLibraries :
.I Array of String
.RS
Import additional Lua libaries.

Example:
.RS
"LuaLibraries": ["math"]
.RE

Available libraries:
.IP \(bu 2
.BR base :
Provides core global functions.
.IP \(bu 2
.BR math :
Provides standard mathematical functions and constants.
.IP \(bu 2
.BR string :
Provides functions for pattern matching and basic string manipulation.
.IP \(bu 2
.BR table :
Provides utilities for creating and manipulating tables (arrays and dictionaries).
.IP \(bu 2
.BR io :
Provides file input/output facilities and stream-based I/O operations.
.IP \(bu 2
.BR os :
Provides operating system interface functions such as time, environment, and process control.
.RE

.PP
.BR FanConfigurations :
.I Array of FanConfiguration
.RS
Array of at least one FanConfiguration
.RE

.PP
.BR RegisterWriteConfigurations :
.I Array of RegisterWriteConfiguration
.RS
Array of RegisterWriteConfiguration
.RE

.SS FanConfiguration
.PP
Defines how NBFC controls a fan.

.PP
.BR FanDisplayName :
.I String
.RS
Sets the fan display name.
.RE

.PP
.BR ReadRegister :
.IR Integer " >= 0 && " Integer " <= 255"
.RS
The register from which NBFC reads the fan speed.

This option is mutually exclusive to
.BR ReadAcpiMethod " and " ReadLuaCode .
Only one of them can be set at a time.
.RE

.PP
.BR ReadAcpiMethod :
.IR String
.RS
The ACPI method for reading the fan speed.

Example:
.RS
"ReadAcpiMethod": "\\\\_SB.PCI0.LPCB.EC0.GFSD"
.RE

This option is mutually exclusive to
.BR ReadRegister " and " ReadLuaCode .
Only one of them can be set at a time.
.RE

.PP
.BR ReadLuaCode :
.IR String " or " "Array of String"
.RS
The Lua code to be executed for reading the fan speed.
.RB See " LUA CODE" .

Example:
.RS
"ReadLuaCode": "return acpi_call(\\"\\\\\\\\_SB.PCI0.LPCB.EC0.GFSD\\")"
.RE

This option is mutually exclusive to
.BR ReadRegister " and " ReadAcpiMethod .
Only one of them can be set at a time.
.RE

.PP
.BR WriteRegister :
.IR Integer " >= 0 && " Integer " <= 255"
.RS
The register which NBFC uses to control the fan.

This option is mutually exclusive to
.BR WriteAcpiMethod " and " WriteLuaCode .
Only one of them can be set at a time.
.RE

.PP
.BR WriteAcpiMethod :
.IR String
.RS
The ACPI method for writing the fan speed. The command must contain a placeholder ($) which will be replaced by the fan speed.

Example:
.RS
"WriteAcpiMethod": "\\\\_SB.PCI0.LPCB.EC0.SFSD $"
.RE

This option is mutually exclusive to
.BR WriteRegister " and " WriteLuaCode .
Only one of them can be set at a time.
.RE

.PP
.BR WriteLuaCode :
.IR String " or " "Array of String"
.RS
The Lua code to execute for writing the fan speed.
.RB See " LUA CODE" .

Example:
.RS
"WriteLuaCode": "return acpi_call(\\"\\\\\\\\_SB.PCI0.LPCB.EC0.SFSD \\" .. get_value())"
.RE

This option is mutually exclusive to
.BR WriteRegister " and " WriteAcpiMethod .
Only one of them can be set at a time.
.RE

.PP
.BR MinSpeedValue :
.IR Integer " >= 0 && " Integer " <= 65535"
.RS
The value which puts the fan to the lowest possible speed (usually this stops the fan). Must be an integer between 0 and 255 or 0 and 65535 if
.B ReadWriteWords
is
.BR true .
Note:
.B MinSpeedValue
does not necessarily have to be smaller than
.BR MaxSpeedValue .
.RE

.PP
.BR MaxSpeedValue :
.IR Integer " >= 0 && " Integer " <= 65535"
.RS
The value which puts the fan to the highest possible fan speed.
.RE

.PP
.BR MinSpeedValueRead :
.IR Integer " >= 0 && " Integer " <= 65535"
.RS
The value which corresponds to the lowest possible fan speed. Will be ignored if
.B IndependentReadMinMaxValues
is
.BR false .
.RE

.PP
.BR MaxSpeedValueRead :
.IR Integer " >= 0 && " Integer " <= 65535"
.RS
The value which corresponds to the highest possible fan speed. Will be ignored if
.B IndependentReadMinMaxValues
is
.BR false .
.RE

.PP
.BR IndependentReadMinMaxValues :
.I Boolean
.RS
Defines if independent minimum/maximum values should be applied for read operations.

This enables
.BR MinSpeedValueRead " and " MaxSpeedValueRead .
.RE

.PP
.BR ResetRequired :
.I Boolean
.RS
Defines if the EC should be reset before the service is shut down.
.RE

.PP
.BR FanSpeedResetValue :
.IR Integer " >= 0 && " Integer " <= 65535"
.RS
Defines the value which will be written to
.B WriteRegister
to reset the EC.

This option is mutually exclusive to
.BR ResetAcpiMethod " and " ResetLuaCode .
Only one of them can be set at a time.
.RE

.PP
.BR ResetAcpiMethod :
.I String
.RS
The ACPI method to call upon fan reset.

This option is mutually exclusive to
.BR FanSpeedResetValue " and " ResetLuaCode .
Only one of them can be set at a time.
.RE

.PP
.BR ResetLuaCode :
.IR String " or " "Array of String"
.RS
The Lua code to be executed upon fan reset.
.RB See " LUA CODE" .

This option is mutually exclusive to
.BR FanSpeedResetValue " and " ResetAcpiMethod .
Only one of them can be set at a time.
.RE

.PP
.BR Sensors :
.I Array of String
.RS
Defines which sensors shall be used for this fan. This should either be a sensor name or a sensor group.

Available groups:
.IP \(bu 2
.BR @CPU :
Uses all sensors named
.BR coretemp ", " k10temp " or " zenpower
.IP \(bu 2
.BR @GPU :
Uses all sensors named
.BR amdgpu ", " nvidia ", " nvidia-ml ", " nouveau " or " radeon
.RE

.PP
.BR TemperatureAlgorithmType :
.I String
.RS
Specify the algorithm type to compute the temperature.
.IP \(bu 2
.BR Average :
Computes the average temperature from all specified sensors (default)
.IP \(bu 2
.BR Min :
Selects the lowest temperature among all specified sensors
.IP \(bu 2
.BR Max :
Selects the highest temperature among all specified sensors
.RE

.PP
.BR TemperatureThresholds :
.I Array of TemperatureThreshold
.RS
Defines how fast the fan runs at different temperatures.
.RE

.PP
.BR FanSpeedPercentageOverrides :
.I Array of FanSpeedPercentageOverride
.RS
Overrides the default algorithm to calculate fan speeds.
.RE

.SS RegisterWriteConfiguration
.PP
Allows to write to any EC register.

.PP
.BR WriteMode :
.I String
.RS
Defines how the value will be written:

.IP \(bu 2
.BR Set :
overwrites the register with the specified value (register = value)
.IP \(bu 2
.BR And :
performs a binary AND operation (register = register & value)
.IP \(bu 2
.BR Or :
performs a binary OR operation (register = register | value)
.IP \(bu 2
.BR Call :
calls the ACPI method stored in
.BR AcpiMethod " or " ResetAcpiMethod
.IP \(bu 2
.BR Lua :
executes the Lua code stored in
.BR LuaCode " or " ResetLuaCode
.RE

.PP
.BR WriteOccasion :
.I String
.RS
Defines when the value should be written:

.IP \(bu 2
.BR OnInitialization :
writes the value once upon initialization (everytime the fan control service starts).
.IP \(bu 2
.BR OnWriteFanSpeed :
writes the value everytime the fan speed is set.
.RE

.PP
.BR Register :
.IR Integer " >= 0 && " Integer " <= 255"
.RS
The register which will be manipulated.
.RE

.PP
.BR Value :
.IR Integer " >= 0 && " Integer " <= 255"
.RS
The value which will be written.

This option is mutually exclusive to
.BR AcpiMethod " and " LuaCode .
Only one of them can be set at a time.
.RE

.PP
.BR AcpiMethod :
.I String
.RS
The ACPI method to call.

This option is mutually exclusive to
.BR Value " and " LuaCode .
Only one of them can be set at a time.
.RE

.PP
.BR LuaCode :
.IR String " or " "Array of String"
.RS
The Lua code to be executed.
.RB See " LUA CODE" .

This option is mutually exclusive to
.BR Value " and " AcpiMethod .
Only one of them can be set at a time.
.RE

.PP
.BR ResetRequired :
.I Boolean
.RS
Defines if the register should be reset before the service is shut down.
.RE

.PP
.BR ResetValue :
.IR Integer " >= 0 && " Integer " <= 255"
.RS
The value which will be written upon reset.

This option is mutually exclusive to
.BR ResetAcpiMethod " and " ResetLuaCode .
Only one of them can be set at a time.
.RE

.PP
.BR ResetAcpiMethod :
.I String
.RS
The ACPI method to call upon reset.

This option is mutually exclusive to
.BR ResetValue " and " ResetLuaCode .
Only one of them can be set at a time.
.RE

.PP
.BR ResetLuaCode :
.IR String " or " "Array of String"
.RS
The Lua code to be executed upon reset.
.RB See " LUA CODE" .

This option is mutually exclusive to
.BR ResetValue " and " ResetAcpiMethod .
Only one of them can be set at a a time.
.RE

.PP
.BR ResetWriteMode :
.I String
.RS
See
.BR WriteMode .
Will only be applied on reset.
.RE

.PP
.BR Description :
.I String
.RS
A short description of what effect the
.B RegisterWriteConfiguration
will have.
.RE

.SS FanSpeedPercentageOverride
.PP
Overrides the default algorithm to calculate fan speeds.

.PP
.BR FanSpeedPercentage :
.IR Float " >= 0.0 && " Float " <= 100.0"
.RS
The fan speed in percent.
.RE

.PP
.BR FanSpeedValue :
.IR Integer " >= 0 && " Integer " <= 65535"
.RS
The fan speed value which will be written to
.BR WriteRegister .
.RE

.PP
.BR TargetOperation :
.I String
.RS
Defines for which operations the speeds should be overridden:

.RS
.IP \(bu 2
.BR Read :
if the value in the EC's ReadRegister is equal to
.BR FanSpeedValue ,
the corresponding percentage will not be calculated, but instead be set to
.BR FanSpeedPercentage .
.IP \(bu 2
.BR Write :
if the target fan speed percentage is equal to
.BR FanSpeedPercentage ,
the corresponding value will not be calculated, but instead be set to
.BR FanSpeedValue .
.IP \(bu 2
.BR ReadWrite :
applies to both, read and write operations.

.RE

.SS TemperatureThreshold
.PP
Defines how fast the fan runs at different temperatures.

.PP
.BR UpThreshold :
.I Integer
.RS
NBFC will select the next upper threshold as soon as the temperature exceeds
.IR UpThreshold " (in celsius)."
.RE

.PP
.BR DownThreshold :
.I Integer
.RS
NBFC will select the next lower threshold as soon as the temperature falls below the
.IR DownThreshold " (in celsius)."
.RE

.PP
.BR FanSpeed :
.IR Float " >= 0.0 && " Float " <= 100.0"
.RS
The fan speed in percent.
.RE

.SH LUA CODE
.PP
NBFC-Linux allows executing
.B Lua
code to implement more complex read or write operations.

Lua code can be specified as either
.RI "a " String " or an " "Array of String" .

.SS Return Values
Every Lua code must return exactly to values:
.BR Error ", " Result.

.B Error
is either
.B nil
(on success) or a
.B string
describing the error (on failure).

.B Result
is an
.B integer
and is used for read operations. For write operations this value is ignored (returning
.B 0
is recommended).

.SS Availabe Lua Functions
The following functions are exposed to Lua:

.BR acpi_call ( method ):
.RS
Executes an ACPI method. Returns
.BR error ", " value " (integer)."
.RE

.BR acpi_call_raw ( method ):
.RS
Executes an ACPI method and returns the raw result as a string. Returns
.BR error ", " value " (string)."
.RE

.BR acpi_get_int ( acpi_result ", " path ):
.RS
Extracts the integer located at
.B path
from an ACPI result. Returns
.BR error ", " value " (integer)."

Example:
.RS
result = "{[0x0, 0x0], [0xFF, 0x0]}"
.br
e, v = acpi_get_int(result, "1 0")
.br
-- v is 0xFF
.RE
.RE

.BR ec_read ( register ):
.RS
Reads a byte from the embedded controller. Returns
.BR error ", " value .
.RE

.BR ec_read_word ( register ):
.RS
Reads two bytes and combines them into a single value. Returns
.BR error ", " value .
.RE

.BR ec_write ( register ", " value ):
.RS
Writes a byte to the embedded controller. Returns
.BR error ", " 0 .
.RE

.BR ec_write_word ( register ", " value ):
.RS
Writes a 16-bit value to a two-byte register. Returns
.BR error ", " 0 .
.RE

.SS Lua Libraries
To keep memory usage as low as possible, no Lua libraries are loaded by default.
They must be explicitly loaded when needed. See
.BR ModelConfig \-> LuaLibraries
for details.

.SH FILES
.PP
.I @SYSCONFDIR@/nbfc/nbfc.json
.RS
The main configuration file for nbfc_service.
.RE

.I @RUNSTATEDIR@/nbfc_service.pid
.RS
File containing the PID of current running nbfc_service.
.RE

.I @RUNSTATEDIR@/nbfc_service.socket
.RS
Socket file of nbfc_service.
.RE

.PP
.I @DATADIR@/nbfc/configs/*.json
.RS
Configuration files for various notebook models.
.RE

.I @DATADIR@/nbfc/model_support.json
.RS
Model support database. This file maps notebook model names to configuration files.
.RE

.I /var/lib/nbfc/configs/*.json
.RS
Configuration files downloaded from the internet. Files in this directory take precedence over those in
.IR @DATADIR@/nbfc/configs .
.RE

.I /var/lib/nbfc/model_support.json
.RS
Model support database downloaded from the internet. Both
.I /var/lib/nbfc/model_support.json
and
.I @DATADIR@/nbfc/model_support.json
are taken into account.
.RE

.I /var/lib/nbfc/state.json
.RS
State file of nbfc_service. This holds the current fan speeds.
.RE

.SH AUTHOR
.PP
Benjamin Abendroth (braph93@gmx.de)

.SH SEE ALSO
.PP
.BR nbfc (1),
.BR nbfc_service (1),
.BR ec_probe (1),
.BR fancontrol (1),
.BR sensors (1)
